            <div type="apparatus">
                <p>PENDING</p>
                 </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p> On December 17 of the fifteenth indiction of the year 6608 died Gephyra, the servant of God.</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Good condition. The painter may have been influenced by spoken language, as it is evident by the use of the word Δηκεβρίω.The words ἐκοιμήθη, and δούλη are misspelled. The fifteenth indiction referred in the inscription does not correspond with the year of 6608 or 1099. According to scholars, the fourteenth century painter wrongly copied the twelfth century dedicatory inscription changing both the indiction and the year. Normally, the indiction 15 corresponds to 6615 and indiction 7 to the year 6608 (<ptr target="Papageorgiou2012b"/>, 53-54, <ptr target="Grivaud2012"/>, 22)</p>
            </div>
